result.execSummary:
The defendant Aubreyona R Woodley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Aubreyona R Woodley in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  Student Intern Rachel Treuer under the supervision of Assistant District Attorney Patrick O'Keefe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: LM  
Case passed and recalled at 10:05am.  Case in court for plea and sentencing hearing. Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Defense counsel and defendant confirms. State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.

Plea hearing held

AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea, court advised the defendant of Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if he is not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived their rights.   Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum and Jury Instruction/Elements of the offense, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.   
Court ordered a DNA sample and advised defendant of applicable surcharge.

Sentencing proceeded.   Statements made as to sentencing.   

Court ordered defendant to serve 5 days in the House of Correction, with 5 days credit for time served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank - surcharge IMPOSED.
Court ordered mandatory costs only, fees and surcharges to be paid by 01-02-2018.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
Upon successful completion of the sentence Court will allow for expungement.
